<!--PageTitleFmt-->
        <div id='wikititle'>
          <div class='pagegroup'><a href='http://wiki.simplelog.net/Themes'>Themes</a> /</div>
          <h1 class='pagetitle'>GettingStarted</h1></div>
<!--PageText-->
<div id='wikitext'>
<p>You have a few options when it comes to themes in <span class='wikiword'>SimpleLog</span>:
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h3>Use the default theme</h3>
<p>This one's the easiest. All you have to do is configure your preferences the way you want them and you're ready to go. The default theme will use your preferences to customize your site wherever it can. Of course, it's a little boring...
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h3>Customize the default theme</h3>
<p>Take it one step further. Use the default theme, set your preferences, then tweak the CSS file stored in themes/simplelog/stylesheets to your linking.
</p>
<div class='vspace'></div><h3>Build your own theme</h3>
<p><a class='wikilink' href='CreateANewTheme'>Creating your own custom theme</a> is the best way to get <span class='wikiword'>SimpleLog</span> looking exactly how you want it. It's pretty easy, too!
</p>
</div>

      </td>
    </tr></table>
